main event: Three round, luminous objects were observed moving slowly at high altitude over Dublin, Georgia on September 3, 1952.
interesting points: The objects were first observed heading west to east, then changed direction 90 degrees to the north.
The objects were observed for about 15 minutes.
The objects appeared elongated and luminous, resembling a flaming or fiery flying saucer.
The light from the objects was steady and did not blink.
The objects maintained a level altitude and did not climb, dive or make any acrobatic maneuvers.
